name: DELIVERY_GAS_SENT
description: This table contains whether cord gasses were sent. This information is entered in Stork's Delivery Summary activity and populated in the delivery record. This information is also copied to the OB_EPT_BH_CRDGASES table in the baby's Patient (EPT) record.

columns.name: SUMMARY_BLOCK_ID
columns.description: The unique identifier (.1 item) for the summary block record.

columns.name: LINE
columns.description: The line number for the information associated with this record. Multiple pieces of information can be associated with this record.

columns.name: DEL_GASES_SENT_YN
columns.description: Stores whether cord gases were sent or not (Y/N). This information is stored in the Delivery Summary.
